    "top_event": "Personnel Injury During Vessel-to-Platform Transfer",
    "incident_type": "Slip/Trip/Fall",
    "costs": null,
    "actions_taken": [
      "Employee evacuated by helicopter to onshore medical facility",
      "Employee placed on restricted work duty",
      "BSEE Lafayette District received notification and requested JSAs, Operating Practices and relevant documents",
      "Cox provided photos, incident report, JSA, employee statement and diagnosis email"
    ],
    "summary": "On 2 August 2022 at approximately 1130 hours, a Cox Operating electrician was injured while attempting to swing from the motor vessel M/V Doug II to the SM 237 #177 satellite platform. The employee placed his left foot on one of five tires used as bumpers on the back of the vessel. As the tires shifted during contact with the platform, the employee's foot slipped between the tires and the boat, resulting in a fractured left foot. The employee was evacuated by helicopter and placed on light duty on 12 September 2022.",
